Jul 20 2009 	Affordable Rates at a Great Location	We had to make a last minute booking since we were attending the Semiconductor convention at Mascone Center. The hotel was like 6 blocks away and the prices were way cheap compared to the hotels nearby the convention center. It took us a mere 16 minute walk to the convention center, and coming back at night we decided to cab it which cost us about $5. We ended up extending our stay to tour san francisco a little bit. Instead of renting a car, the frontdesk clerk MIKE advised us to use public transportation which were footsteps to the property. And guided us to the main attractions to see in San Francsico and also recommended some hidden Gems spots that not a lot of tourists knew about. I was very impressed with his knowledge of San Francisco. Rooms are decent the room we had a microwave and a small fridge and high speed internet was free. The only thing the property was lacking were ground floor rooms. The property is structured were the ground floor is designated for the FREE parking. We enjoyed our stay, and if any of you are lucky to bump into MIKE make sure you pick his BRAIN!!We will be back for sure!	
