Mar 25 2007 	Awefull!!	Our experience was so bad, I'm not sure even where to start. I booked my family and I (My husband and three children, ages 1,7,9) online for a four night stay as part of our yearly vacation. I've never stayed here, or at any other Howard Johnson before, but from what I've heard and read, I assumed it would be okay. Ad list free parking, but there is only about 6-8 spots on street level, plus only one way to get in and out. You have to back out into trafic from an enclosed garage. Next, the &quot;locked&quot; gate to get access to rooms above was broken and did not lock. NOT safe. I requested a non smoking room, and after hauling our children and luggage up a flight of stairs, found we were booked into a smoking room. After complaint, we were moved to the third floor. So after hefting children/bags up another flight of stairs (there's no elevator by the way), our second rm was smoke free. However, moulding was broken off above the door, two of the four lamps in the room did not work, the bathroom must have had at least 2 or 3 different kinds of tiles. There were rips in coverlets and the room just felt unclean. When looking out the window, we could see a huge deserted parking lot, and seperating us was an alley that had all sorts of graffiti, garbage and homeless people. We were literally checked in, and checked back out in 10 minutes. They refused to give me a full refund, charged me for one nights stay ($125). I wouldn't pay $50 to stay there and i will NEVER stay at a Howard Johnson again because of my experience here.	
Jan 15 2007	Not bad	Not bad for a budget hotel. Area isnt as bad as other parts of the city, after all it is San francisco! The hotel is secure, with a security gate at bottom floor to give access to only key holders. (no elevator which is typically expected with smaller hotels i guess) Rooms are clean, impressed with the granite bathroom counter tops. Sink and toilet separate. The rooms arent as big but incorporate all the necessities to make our stary affordable, safe, comfortable and peaceful. The noice wasnt bad at all, surprising we were concerened with the traffic on the streets but actually it stayed quiet and traffic does quiet down after rush hour. Housekeeping friendly. Office staff proficient and friendly, helpful with directions and recommendations. if ur looking for a affordable place to stay this is not a bad choice, I would stay there again.	
